verbose_text: Therefore, PCT levels> = 0.5 ng/mL were considered as a positive result according to Schuetz et al. 11 The WBC count (> 10.0 x 10 9 / L as a positive result) and the neutrophil ratio (> 70% as a positive result) were estimated by using the Automatic Blood Cell Analyzer (SYSMEX XE-2100; Sysmex, Kobe, Japan).
